PyRIT — Python Risk Identification Tool for generative AI
================================================================================

  Project:  https://github.com/microsoft/PyRIT
  License:  MIT
  Pip extra: `pip install rai-toolkit[pyrit]`
  Used by:  integrations/pyrit_integration/adapter.py — subclasses
            `pyrit.prompt_target.PromptTarget`, consumes
            `pyrit.models.AttackOutcome` / `Message`, and initializes
            `pyrit.memory.CentralMemory`. The adapter translates PyRIT
            attack runs into the toolkit's RedTeamReport shape. The
            default `rai assess` path does not invoke this adapter; it
            is reachable when callers opt into the PyRIT source through
            the assessment API or import it explicitly.

If you publish work that relies on this adapter, the PyRIT authors ask
that you cite their paper:

  @misc{munoz2024pyritframeworksecurityrisk,
        title={PyRIT: A Framework for Security Risk Identification
               and Red Teaming in Generative AI Systems},
        author={Gary D. Lopez Munoz and Amanda J. Minnich and
                Roman Lutz and Richard Lundeen and Raja Sekhar
                Rao Dheekonda and Nina Chikanov and
                Bolor-Erdene Jagdagdorj and Martin Pouliot and
                Shiven Chawla and Whitney Maxwell and Blake
                Bullwinkel and Katherine Pratt and Joris de
                Gruyter and Charlotte Siska and Pete Bryan and
                Tori Westerhoff and Chang Kawaguchi and
                Christian Seifert and Ram Shankar Siva Kumar and
                Yonatan Zunger},
        year={2024},
        eprint={2410.02828},
        archivePrefix={arXiv},
        primaryClass={cs.CR},
        url={https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.02828},
  }

The tool itself is also citable via the upstream CITATION.cff entry
(https://github.com/microsoft/PyRIT/blob/main/CITATION.cff):

  Microsoft AI Red Team. PyRIT: The Python Risk Identification Tool
  for generative AI. https://github.com/microsoft/PyRIT,
  doi:10.48550/arXiv.2410.02828, 2024.

================================================================================
Garak — Generative AI Red-teaming & Assessment Kit
================================================================================

  Project:  https://github.com/NVIDIA/garak
  License:  Apache-2.0
  Pip extra: `pip install rai-toolkit[garak]`
  Used by:  integrations/garak_integration/adapter.py — wraps selected
            Garak probes with a toolkit BaseModel-backed generator and
            translates probe results into the toolkit's RedTeamReport shape.
            The default `rai assess` path does not invoke this adapter; it
            is reachable when callers opt into the Garak source through
            the assessment API or import it explicitly.

If you publish work that relies on this adapter, cite the Garak paper
requested by the upstream project:

  @article{garak,
    title={{garak: A Framework for Security Probing Large Language Models}},
    author={Leon Derczynski and Erick Galinkin and Jeffrey Martin and
            Subho Majumdar and Nanna Inie},
    year={2024},
    howpublished={\url{https://garak.ai}}
  }


